28:44.388 --> 28:46.958
has what it takes to fool
Penn and Teller.

28:46.990 --> 28:49.760
[fireworks booming]

28:49.794 --> 28:52.230
- Magic was my escape
from reality.

28:52.262 --> 28:54.566
As a kid on the weekends,
we slept on the floor,

28:54.598 --> 28:57.367
because there were gunshots
all through the night.

28:57.402 --> 29:00.171
We were surrounded
by gang culture and drugs.

29:00.204 --> 29:02.740
I was raised by my mother.
She was a social worker

29:02.773 --> 29:04.742
and would take in kids
that needed help

29:04.776 --> 29:06.678
and try to get them
to think differently.

29:06.711 --> 29:09.213
Most of my childhood friends
either OD'd,

29:09.247 --> 29:11.648
ended up in prison,
or died violent deaths,

29:11.682 --> 29:14.652
except for the ones
she'd helped.

29:14.685 --> 29:18.056
Living your dreams
is a very rare thing.

29:18.088 --> 29:20.057
I have a weekly show
in Wisconsin.

29:20.090 --> 29:21.659
And I've been on
the national tour.

29:21.692 --> 29:23.928
I make a great living
doing magic.

29:23.961 --> 29:25.663
I've done things that no one
ever thought

29:25.696 --> 29:27.065
I would accomplish.

29:27.097 --> 29:28.633
This is definitely
one of them.

29:28.665 --> 29:31.269
Very grateful to be
where I am today.

29:31.301 --> 29:32.737
I get to do what I love,

29:32.770 --> 29:34.972
make my mother proud
before she passed last year.

29:35.006 --> 29:37.008
So that meant a lot to me.

29:37.040 --> 29:39.376
If I fool Penn and Teller,
I will accomplish something

29:39.410 --> 29:42.146
that even
I didn't know I could do.

29:42.180 --> 29:46.116
[cheers and applause]

29:46.151 --> 29:50.555
- Give it up for
the magical Matthew Teague.

29:50.587 --> 29:56.294
[cheers and applause]

29:56.326 --> 29:57.662
- I'd heard of tricks.

29:57.694 --> 30:01.031
But when I was 12 years old,
I saw magic for real.

30:01.065 --> 30:02.599
I found out that part
of the secret was in a book

30:02.634 --> 30:05.002
written by a guy
named David Roth.

30:05.036 --> 30:08.105
I was surrounded by a lot of
negative influences growing up.

30:08.138 --> 30:11.976
Magic kept me out of trouble
and probably saved my life.

30:12.009 --> 30:13.778
We lost David this year,
so I was never able to tell him

30:13.811 --> 30:17.981
the impact that he had on me.
But, David, this one's for you.

30:18.016 --> 30:20.984
[light instrumental music]

30:21.019 --> 30:26.257
♪ ♪

30:26.290 --> 30:27.858
[applause]

30:27.892 --> 30:34.932
♪ ♪

30:44.843 --> 30:46.544
[audience exclaims]

30:46.577 --> 30:50.582
[applause]

30:50.615 --> 30:55.886
♪ ♪

30:55.920 --> 30:59.490
[applause]

30:59.523 --> 31:06.530
♪ ♪

31:07.065 --> 31:09.032
[audience exclaims]

31:09.067 --> 31:11.669
[applause]

31:11.702 --> 31:17.040
♪ ♪

31:17.075 --> 31:19.611
[applause]

31:19.644 --> 31:26.683
♪ ♪

31:57.781 --> 32:00.652
[cheers and applause]

32:00.684 --> 32:04.955
- Matthew Teague.

32:04.989 --> 32:06.723
That was so cool.

32:06.758 --> 32:08.026
- Oh, thank you so much.

32:08.058 --> 32:09.928
- Yeah. It's like watching
your hands dance.

32:09.961 --> 32:12.130
- Oh, wow. That's kinda what
the goal is, you know?

32:12.163 --> 32:13.498
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

32:13.530 --> 32:15.365
- Magic has been a pretty
powerful force in your life.

32:15.400 --> 32:16.733
- Absolutely. Yeah.

32:16.768 --> 32:18.869
It's been the ongoing passion
throughout my life.

32:18.903 --> 32:20.438
I was really into, you know,

32:20.471 --> 32:22.406
writing raps
and poetry growing up,

32:22.440 --> 32:24.442
but magic just
kind of stuck with me.

32:24.474 --> 32:28.011
Magic was just
like medicine for me.

32:28.046 --> 32:30.781
It was kind of an escape,
you know, and allowed me

32:30.815 --> 32:35.153
to make friends, of course,
and defuse situations at times.

32:35.185 --> 32:36.887
But it was, I don't know,
always with me.

32:36.921 --> 32:38.890
It was like an ace
in the back pocket.

32:38.923 --> 32:40.590
- I'm sure it helped
to have something

32:40.625 --> 32:41.759
you were passionate about.

32:41.792 --> 32:42.759
- Absolutely. Yeah.

32:42.794 --> 32:43.861
Well, my mom's support too.

32:43.894 --> 32:45.663
My mom was like
an amazing woman.

32:45.697 --> 32:46.864
You know, I always wanted
to thank her

32:46.897 --> 32:48.700
on national television.
- Here you are.

32:48.732 --> 32:50.401
- So, Mom, thanks so much
for everything,

32:50.434 --> 32:52.804
all you sacrificed
to get me here.

32:52.836 --> 32:54.404
Definitely couldn't have
done it without you.

32:54.439 --> 32:56.307
- Do you mainly do
close-up magic?

32:56.340 --> 32:58.041
- I perform at a casino
in Wisconsin.

32:58.076 --> 32:59.876
So I would do stage show
maybe every six months

32:59.911 --> 33:03.146
and then would do strolling
throughout the casino.

33:03.181 --> 33:04.816
Yeah, I've been doing that
for almost nine years now.

33:04.848 --> 33:06.750
- Does the casino get
a little nervous

33:06.784 --> 33:10.020
at how good you are
at hiding money?

33:10.054 --> 33:11.622
- I'm very selective
with what I show them.

33:11.655 --> 33:13.057
- Okay, figured.

33:13.090 --> 33:14.258
- Not a lot of
gambling routines.

33:14.291 --> 33:15.792
- They might be watching you
extra close

33:15.826 --> 33:17.494
after they see this episode.

33:17.528 --> 33:19.596
- You know, but they've gotten
to know me by now.

33:19.630 --> 33:20.798
So I'd like to think

33:20.832 --> 33:22.767
that they kind of
maybe somewhat trust me.

33:22.799 --> 33:24.935
- Yeah.
- But, you know, so it's good.

33:24.969 --> 33:27.005
- All right, Matthew.
Well, let's see

33:27.038 --> 33:29.307
if your close-up magic
fooled Penn and Teller.

33:29.339 --> 33:30.775
- Sounds great.

33:30.807 --> 33:32.876
- Oh, Matthew,
what a great routine.

33:32.910 --> 33:34.412
Just beautiful.

33:34.444 --> 33:38.615
The one--the one-handed stuff
moving around is so, so great.

33:38.648 --> 33:40.785
Usually,
when I do these things,

33:40.817 --> 33:44.756
talking to people,
I have to sneak in a name

33:44.788 --> 33:46.691
or I
have to try to talk in code.

33:46.723 --> 33:48.859
But you laid it all out there
at the beginning.

33:48.893 --> 33:50.127
You said David Roth.

33:50.161 --> 33:53.330
- Yeah.
- And you told us everything.

33:53.364 --> 33:54.932
And we want to tell you
something back,

33:54.965 --> 33:56.800
which is we knew David.

33:56.834 --> 33:58.970
And we were lucky enough
to have him on the show.

33:59.002 --> 34:00.304
- Yeah.

34:00.337 --> 34:01.772
- And you wanted to do this
as a tribute to him.

34:01.806 --> 34:03.007
He would have loved you.

34:03.040 --> 34:05.042
- Man, yeah, I wish I got
to--to meet him.

34:05.076 --> 34:06.877
- Yeah, he would have
absolutely loved you,

34:06.911 --> 34:08.445
'cause all those moves are done

34:08.478 --> 34:11.114
just perfectly,
just beautifully.

34:11.148 --> 34:13.583
And I'll tell you, when you
went to the one-handed thing,

34:13.617 --> 34:14.952
I just loved that.

34:14.985 --> 34:18.322
What a great, great,
great magical look.

34:18.356 --> 34:21.893
And what a really nice style,
and the tempo and everything

34:21.925 --> 34:24.896
was beautiful, just gorgeous.
I can't compliment you enough.

34:24.929 --> 34:27.664
The other thing you did is,
most people

34:27.697 --> 34:30.735
that do this kind of thing,
they do behind a big table,

34:30.768 --> 34:33.938
which as we all know
covers a multitude of sins.

34:33.971 --> 34:35.005
- Yeah.

34:35.039 --> 34:36.474
- Just having that thing
on your lap

34:36.507 --> 34:39.277
and out there so naked and pure

34:39.309 --> 34:41.579
and just you
and the short sleeves

34:41.612 --> 34:43.614
and the coins
and going to work.

34:43.648 --> 34:45.750
So we just couldn't
love you more.

34:45.782 --> 34:48.652
We know that David Roth
would have loved you.

34:48.686 --> 34:50.454
And we know the stuff
that you know.

34:50.487 --> 34:52.123
So I don't think you fooled us.

34:52.155 --> 34:54.858
But boy
we absolutely love you.

34:54.891 --> 34:56.661
- Oh, thanks so much for having
me on the show, you guys.

34:56.693 --> 34:58.362
This is an amazing experience.

34:58.396 --> 34:59.730
So I just really
appreciate it so much.

34:59.764 --> 35:01.065
- Aw, thank you.

35:01.099 --> 35:03.534
- Thank you, guys. Thank you.
Thank you so much.

35:03.568 --> 35:04.534
- Matthew Teague!

35:04.568 --> 35:07.637
[applause]

35:07.672 --> 35:10.541
Now it's time for my favorite
part of the show,

35:10.574 --> 35:14.277
getting these guys out of those
chairs and up on this stage.

35:14.311 --> 35:17.181
See Penn and Teller perform
when we come back.

35:17.215 --> 35:20.184
[jazz music]

35:20.217 --> 35:21.719
♪ ♪

35:25.021 --> 35:27.992
[jazz music]

35:28.025 --> 35:29.092
♪ ♪

35:29.126 --> 35:30.327
- Welcome back.

35:30.360 --> 35:33.030
Like the Beatles
sometimes Penn and Teller

35:33.063 --> 35:35.766
get by with a little help
from their friends.

35:35.800 --> 35:38.034
This next trick was created
with the help

35:38.068 --> 35:40.972
of four-time fooler Jandro.

35:41.005 --> 35:42.440
Closing out our show,

35:42.472 --> 35:45.543
the Las Vegas legends
themselves,

35:45.576 --> 35:47.344
Penn and Teller.

35:47.378 --> 35:49.713
[cheers and applause]

35:49.746 --> 35:52.048
- You know, sometimes Teller
and I do a bit

35:52.083 --> 35:54.385
where there's only
one of us onstage.

35:54.418 --> 35:57.420
We always write the stuff
and work on it and direct it

35:57.454 --> 35:59.724
and everything together.
But this is a trick

35:59.757 --> 36:01.291
that I really
didn't have much to do with.

36:01.324 --> 36:02.693
I mean,
I was talked through it,

36:02.726 --> 36:04.195
I walked through it,
but it really

36:04.228 --> 36:06.998
is Jandro and Teller
worked this whole thing out

36:07.030 --> 36:10.635
and it's called Whack-a-Teller.
Or there it is in Spanish,

36:10.668 --> 36:12.536
which means kind of meathead.
[laughter]

36:12.570 --> 36:15.005
And you've got five numbers
in front of you, Alyson.

36:15.039 --> 36:17.375
See the five numbers?
Mix them up, shuffle them up,

36:17.407 --> 36:18.943
cut them up,
all you want to do,

36:18.976 --> 36:20.878
just keep them really mixed up
and sorted up,

36:20.911 --> 36:23.280
'cause you and I
are kind of in this together.

36:23.313 --> 36:25.983
Okay, Teller and Jandro
put the trick together.

36:26.016 --> 36:28.219
But you and I
are kind of the spectators.

36:28.251 --> 36:29.987
We're the ones that are
kind of helping out.

36:30.021 --> 36:31.489
We're the ones
with the numbers.

36:31.521 --> 36:33.423
[upbeat Latin-tinged music]

36:33.456 --> 36:36.760
That's the Spanish
music starting, I guess.

36:36.793 --> 36:38.762
Very Spanish.

36:38.795 --> 36:44.568
♪ ♪

36:44.601 --> 36:46.903
Now, I'm gonna pull one
of these numbers--okay,

36:46.938 --> 36:49.773
I'll get out of the way first.

36:49.806 --> 36:56.847
♪ ♪

36:59.916 --> 37:00.985
[laughter]

37:01.018 --> 37:03.653
Good. So I'm gonna put
one number here.

37:03.688 --> 37:07.625
So four of these
are obviously not Teller,

37:07.657 --> 37:10.460
and one of them is Teller.

37:10.494 --> 37:12.530
And you've mixed them up,
and you've cut them up, and...

37:12.563 --> 37:13.731
♪ ♪

37:13.764 --> 37:14.731
Okay, good. More music.

37:14.764 --> 37:17.134
More music.

37:17.168 --> 37:19.836
Thank you, Zeke.

37:19.869 --> 37:22.907
♪ ♪

37:22.940 --> 37:25.443
Thanks.

37:25.476 --> 37:26.811
- Hey.

37:26.844 --> 37:28.512
[applause]

37:28.545 --> 37:30.248
As I said, it's called
Whack-a-Teller.

37:30.280 --> 37:32.148
And you're gonna
pick the numbers

37:32.182 --> 37:35.786
and I'm gonna smash
the numbers you choose.

37:35.820 --> 37:37.554
And one of them
is actually Teller.

37:37.588 --> 37:39.889
And this is a real
big heavy hammer.

37:39.923 --> 37:41.192
It's a wicked heavy hammer.

37:41.224 --> 37:42.927
So you shuffled them up, right?
You cut them up?

37:42.960 --> 37:44.195
- Yeah, yeah.
- You're all set.

37:44.228 --> 37:46.197
So just turn over
the first one.

37:46.230 --> 37:47.998
What number is it?

37:48.032 --> 37:52.836
- Four.
- Four. Okay, four. So...hup!

37:52.869 --> 37:54.338
[audience exclaims]

37:54.371 --> 37:56.806
And that's the way
the trick goes. Next one.

37:56.840 --> 37:59.610
- Uh, three.

37:59.643 --> 38:01.344
- Okay, three.

38:01.378 --> 38:03.648
Okay, well, I would be--I
should be able to do that.

38:03.681 --> 38:08.619
But I just want to make sure.
And here we go. And...hup!

38:08.652 --> 38:09.786
[audience exclaims]

38:09.820 --> 38:11.588
There we go.
Yes, it's exciting.

38:11.621 --> 38:12.889
I mean, he did a good job
writing this.

38:12.922 --> 38:15.992
There's no doubt about it.
I also want to say

38:16.027 --> 38:18.829
very clearly
that in terms of culpability

38:18.862 --> 38:21.032
a heavy hammer,
human head up here,

38:21.065 --> 38:24.568
Teller's head, I would say,
Jandro, it's his idea,

38:24.601 --> 38:26.269
and, Teller,
they're responsible.

38:26.304 --> 38:28.371
We're kind of out
of this entirely.

38:28.405 --> 38:29.907
[laughter]
Next number, please.

38:29.940 --> 38:32.710
- Uh, five.
- Five, okay.

38:32.742 --> 38:34.679
- So five's
way over, here of course.

38:34.711 --> 38:38.648
And okay, five.

38:38.682 --> 38:40.483
The body cam footage
will show all this

38:40.518 --> 38:41.719
that I have
nothing--here we go.

38:41.751 --> 38:44.588
[laughter]
And hup!

38:44.621 --> 38:45.722
[audience exclaims]

38:45.755 --> 38:47.257
- Oh!

38:47.291 --> 38:51.528
- For the next one, we don't
want Teller to hear the number

38:51.561 --> 38:53.331
and, like, get up and run away.

38:53.364 --> 38:54.898
[laughter]
So don't say it out loud.

38:54.931 --> 38:56.733
Okay, just hold it up
so I can see it.

38:56.766 --> 38:58.268
I also want to
make it clear again.

38:58.302 --> 39:01.539
Jandro's--it's only down
to two people, heavy hammer.

39:01.572 --> 39:04.608
One of these
is Teller's head in it.

39:04.641 --> 39:06.476
Jandro is responsible,
Teller's responsible,

39:06.510 --> 39:08.411
then, of course, everybody
at home knows that

39:08.445 --> 39:10.748
Alyson picked all the numbers.

39:10.780 --> 39:12.315
[laughter]

39:12.349 --> 39:15.786
So, um, next one, don't say it,
Alyson, but it's your choice.

39:15.820 --> 39:20.257
Okay, and yeah, all right.
Okay, fine.

39:20.291 --> 39:21.759
Here we go.

39:25.195 --> 39:28.231
And hup!

39:28.264 --> 39:29.500
[audience exclaims]
- Oh!

39:29.532 --> 39:30.800
[applause]

39:30.835 --> 39:31.902
- That's a good trick.

39:31.936 --> 39:33.938
I mean, Jandro and Teller
did a great job.

39:33.971 --> 39:35.639
What's the next one,
the last one to make sure?

39:35.672 --> 39:37.775
Yeah, okay.
I just want to say, Alyson,

39:37.807 --> 39:39.275
you were getting
very nervous during that.

39:39.309 --> 39:40.844
- Yeah.

39:40.878 --> 39:42.213
- You've been doing this show
long enough. You show know that

39:42.246 --> 39:44.547
there's all sorts of ways
to accomplish this.

39:44.581 --> 39:48.552
You know, there was--I mean,
I figure there's a big drop

39:48.585 --> 39:50.086
down there behind there.

39:50.121 --> 39:52.422
They could have switched him
out or during the choreography,

39:52.456 --> 39:56.226
so these are all dummies,
'cause we couldn't control you.

39:56.260 --> 39:58.396
You picked any numbers
you wanted. You did all that.

39:58.429 --> 40:02.800
So this too is also a dummy,
and we'll just whack this one

40:02.833 --> 40:05.034
and then we'll bring
Teller out and...hup!

40:05.068 --> 40:06.670
- Penn! Penn! Penn!

40:06.704 --> 40:07.905
[laughter]

40:07.938 --> 40:09.340
Are you out
of you [...] mind?

40:09.373 --> 40:11.208
- [laughs]

40:11.242 --> 40:15.278
- Wow.
That's a really good trick.

40:15.311 --> 40:20.016
♪ ♪

40:20.050 --> 40:21.318
[castanets clacking]

40:21.351 --> 40:22.786
- Oh, man.

40:22.820 --> 40:25.322
